						<summary>

						<p>On a slab in the Kāmākshi-amman Sannidhi street.</p>						

						<p>Dated in Śaka 1709 (read in A.R. as 1706), <hi rend="italic">Krōdhi, Chaitra</hi> śu. 15, Monday. Late inscription.</p>						

						<p>States that Venkaṭēśvara Pauṇḍrika, son of Abbājī-Paṇḍita (?) and grandson of Jaggannadīkshita of Āpastaṁba-<hi rend="italic">sūtra</hi> and Yajus-<hi rend="italic">śākhā</hi> performed the <hi rend="italic">Mahāgnichayana</hi> sacrifice.</p>						

						</summary>
